==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|acidité|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|aciditātem|lang=la}}, accusative singular of {{term|aciditas|aciditās|sourness, acidity|lang=la}}, from {{term|acidus||sour, acid|lang=la}}. See [[acid]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|acidities}}

# The [[quality]] or state of being acid
# The quality of [[sour]]; [[sourness]]; [[tartness]]; [[sharpness]] to the taste, as in the '''acidity''' of lemon juice.
#: ''Empty stomachs lead to '''acidity''' and leave a sour taste in the mouth.''
# ''Med.'' Excessive acid quality, as in [[gastric]] [[secretions]].

